{"view":"article","slug":"f2l-convertors","category":"3x3","subcategory":null,"topDir":"3x3","title":{"en":"F2L Convertors: Commutator Scrambles","zh":"F2L转换机: 换位子打乱"},"content":{"en":"<p><img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image2.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><strong><img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image4.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></strong><img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image6.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"><a id=\"_Hlk54563012\"></a><strong>F2L Convertors: Commutator Scrambles</strong></p><p>Useful mainly in these situations: Generating F2L cases uniformly; Converting some F2L case directly to a new F2L case from without solving the original one ; Generating F2L cases while preserve as many pieces as possible (for example, Multislotting, EOLS, <a href=\"/tutorial/ols\" class=\"see-also-link\" data-see-also=\"true\">OLS</a>); One is not familiar with normal F2L scramble algs.</p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><p><strong>Convertors</strong></p><p>Algs are from 3BLD 3-style edge (corner) and flip (twist) algs.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>E+<img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image8.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td><td><p>E-<img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image10.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td><td><p>F<img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image12.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td><td><p>S<img src=\"/stats/tutorial/media/f2l-convertors/en/image14.svg\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span class=\"tutorial-chip\" data-alg=\"R' S2 R U' R' S2 R\"><strong>R' S2 R U' R' S2 R</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span class=\"tutorial-chip\" data-alg=\"R S' R' U' R S R'\"><strong>R S' R' U' R S R'</strong></span></p></td><td><p><span class=\"tutorial-chip\" data-alg=\"R S' R' U R S R2' S2 R U' R' S2 R\"><strong>R S' R' U R S R2' S2 R